arts.ttl: Colchester United drew with Harrogate Town in League Two
arts.sum: Harry Anderson's shot fizzed past the near post from 20 yards for Colchester while at the other end, Harrogate substitute Ellis Taylor went close with a half volley, as both sides pushed for a winner but the spoils were shared. Chances were few and far between in the first half, although Ellis Iandolo did hook a shot wide of the target off balance for Colchester midway through the first half, after Fiacre Kelleher had helped Payne's corner into his path in the area.
Neither goalkeeper was beaten in the League Two clash.

arts.ttl: Colchester United fan Si Collinson gives his U's views
arts.sum: So, after the Cheltenham game and others we have seen this season, it was refreshing to witness a match where the officials showed how it should be done. This in turn then means the job of officiating games is not very appealing to new people, with fewer and fewer new individuals picking up the whistle.

arts.ttl: Colchester United boss Danny Cowley on Harrogate Town game
arts.sum: “I think we’ve got a really good group and they come in with the ambition every day of trying to be better than yesterday. Colchester lie two points and four places above Harrogate in the table and boss Cowley said: “For us now, it’s to try to back it up.

arts.ttl: TRANSFER WINDOW: Colchester United sign Tyreece Simpson on loan from Stevenage
arts.sum: He made 30 appearances for the Robins, scoring 11 times before returning to Ipswich and then joined Huddersfield Town in September, 2022, signing a four-year deal. Simpson spent the season on loan at Northampton Town last season, making 44 league and cup appearances for the Cobblers and scoring six times.
